**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
// secure_admin_controller.php

require_once 'database.php';
require_once 'auth_service.php';
require_once 'audit_logger.php';

class SecureAdminController {
    private $pdo;
    private $authService;
    private $auditLogger;

    public function __construct($pdo, AuthService $authService, AuditLogger $auditLogger) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
        $this->authService = $authService;
        $this->auditLogger = $auditLogger;
    }

    // Centralized authorization check
    private function requireRole(string $requiredRole): void {
        // First: Verify session is valid
        if (!$this->authService->isAuthenticated()) {
            $this->auditLogger->logUnauthorizedAccess($_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'], 'unauthenticated');
            http_response_code(401);
            throw new UnauthorizedException('Authentication required');
        }

        // Second: Verify user has required role
        $currentUser = $this->authService->getCurrentUser();
        if (!$this->authService->hasRole($currentUser['id'], $requiredRole)) {
            $this->auditLogger->logUnauthorizedAccess($currentUser['id'], "missing_role:$requiredRole");
            http_response_code(403);
            throw new ForbiddenException('Insufficient privileges');
        }
    }

    public function getAllUsers(): string {
        // Enforce admin role before any operation
        $this->requireRole('admin');

        $currentUser = $this->authService->getCurrentUser();
        $this->auditLogger->log($currentUser['id'], 'admin_view_all_users');

        $stmt = $this->pdo->query("SELECT id, username, email, role, created_at FROM users");
        return json_encode($stmt->fetchAll(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC));
    }

    public function deleteUser(int $userId): string {
        $this->requireRole('super_admin'); // Higher privilege required

        $currentUser = $this->authService->getCurrentUser();

        // Prevent self-deletion
        if ($currentUser['id'] === $userId) {
            throw new BadRequestException('Cannot delete your own account');
        }

        $this->auditLogger->log($currentUser['id'], 'admin_delete_user', ['target_user' => $userId]);

        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare("DELETE FROM users WHERE id = ?");
        $stmt->execute([$userId]);

        return json_encode(['status' => 'success']);
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Authentication verification**: Every request validates the session token before processing
- **Role-based access control (RBAC)**: Each function explicitly requires specific roles
- **Centralized authorization**: Single `requireRole()` method ensures consistent checks
- **Audit logging**: All access attempts (successful and failed) are logged for forensics
- **Principle of least privilege**: Different actions require different permission levels

Excellent question! Resource-level authorization (also called Attribute-Based Access Control or ABAC) is essential for real applications. You need to check both the user's role AND their relationship to the resource. This is where many applications fail, even when they have basic role checks.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```php
<?php
// authorization_service.php - Production-ready ABAC implementation

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Security;

use App\Models\User;
use App\Models\Resource;
use App\Logging\SecurityAuditLogger;
use App\Cache\PermissionCache;

class AuthorizationService {
    private SecurityAuditLogger $auditLogger;
    private PermissionCache $permissionCache;
    private array $policyHandlers = [];

    public function __construct(
        SecurityAuditLogger $auditLogger,
        PermissionCache $permissionCache
    ) {
        $this->auditLogger = $auditLogger;
        $this->permissionCache = $permissionCache;
        $this->registerDefaultPolicies();
    }

    // Register resource-specific policy handlers
    private function registerDefaultPolicies(): void {
        $this->policyHandlers['user_profile'] = new UserProfilePolicy();
        $this->policyHandlers['document'] = new DocumentPolicy();
        $this->policyHandlers['order'] = new OrderPolicy();
    }

    /**
     * Main authorization check - use this everywhere
     */
    public function authorize(
        User $actor,
        string $action,
        string $resourceType,
        ?int $resourceId = null,
        array $context = []
    ): AuthorizationResult {

        $startTime = microtime(true);

        // Layer 1: Check if user is authenticated and active
        if (!$actor->isActive()) {
            return $this->deny($actor, $action, $resourceType, $resourceId, 'account_inactive');
        }

        // Layer 2: Check cached permissions for performance
        $cacheKey = $this->buildCacheKey($actor->getId(), $action, $resourceType, $resourceId);
        $cached = $this->permissionCache->get($cacheKey);
        if ($cached !== null) {
            return $cached;
        }

        // Layer 3: Super admin bypass (use sparingly!)
        if ($actor->hasRole('super_admin') && $this->isSuperAdminAllowed($action)) {
            return $this->allow($actor, $action, $resourceType, $resourceId, 'super_admin_override');
        }

        // Layer 4: Check role-based permissions
        if (!$this->hasRolePermission($actor, $action, $resourceType)) {
            return $this->deny($actor, $action, $resourceType, $resourceId, 'role_denied');
        }

        // Layer 5: Check resource-specific policy (ownership, department, etc.)
        if ($resourceId !== null && isset($this->policyHandlers[$resourceType])) {
            $policy = $this->policyHandlers[$resourceType];
            $result = $policy->evaluate($actor, $action, $resourceId, $context);

            $this->permissionCache->set($cacheKey, $result, ttl: 300);
            $this->logAuthorizationDecision($actor, $action, $resourceType, $resourceId, $result, $startTime);

            return $result;
        }

        // Default deny
        return $this->deny($actor, $action, $resourceType, $resourceId, 'no_matching_policy');
    }

    private function deny(
        User $actor,
        string $action,
        string $resourceType,
        ?int $resourceId,
        string $reason
    ): AuthorizationResult {
        $result = new AuthorizationResult(false, $reason);
        $this->auditLogger->logDeniedAccess(
            $actor->getId(),
            $action,
            $resourceType,
            $resourceId,
            $reason,
            $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown'
        );
        return $result;
    }

    private function allow(
        User $actor,
        string $action,
        string $resourceType,
        ?int $resourceId,
        string $reason
    ): AuthorizationResult {
        return new AuthorizationResult(true, $reason);
    }

    private function logAuthorizationDecision(
        User $actor,
        string $action,
        string $resourceType,
        ?int $resourceId,
        AuthorizationResult $result,
        float $startTime
    ): void {
        $duration = (microtime(true) - $startTime) * 1000;

        $this->auditLogger->logAuthzDecision([
            'actor_id' => $actor->getId(),
            'action' => $action,
            'resource_type' => $resourceType,
            'resource_id' => $resourceId,
            'decision' => $result->isAllowed() ? 'ALLOW' : 'DENY',
            'reason' => $result->getReason(),
            'duration_ms' => $duration,
            'ip_address' => $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown',
            'user_agent' => $_SERVER['HTTP_USER_AGENT'] ?? 'unknown',
            'timestamp' => date('c')
        ]);
    }
}

// user_profile_policy.php - Resource-specific policy
class UserProfilePolicy {

    public function evaluate(
        User $actor,
        string $action,
        int $resourceId,
        array $context
    ): AuthorizationResult {

        switch ($action) {
            case 'view':
                return $this->canView($actor, $resourceId);
            case 'edit':
                return $this->canEdit($actor, $resourceId);
            case 'delete':
                return $this->canDelete($actor, $resourceId);
            default:
                return new AuthorizationResult(false, 'unknown_action');
        }
    }

    private function canView(User $actor, int $profileId): AuthorizationResult {
        // Users can view their own profile
        if ($actor->getId() === $profileId) {
            return new AuthorizationResult(true, 'owner');
        }

        // Admins can view any profile
        if ($actor->hasRole('admin')) {
            return new AuthorizationResult(true, 'admin_privilege');
        }

        // HR can view profiles in their department
        if ($actor->hasRole('hr_manager')) {
            $targetUser = User::find($profileId);
            if ($targetUser && $targetUser->getDepartmentId() === $actor->getDepartmentId()) {
                return new AuthorizationResult(true, 'department_hr');
            }
        }

        return new AuthorizationResult(false, 'no_view_permission');
    }

    private function canEdit(User $actor, int $profileId): AuthorizationResult {
        // Users can edit their own profile (but not role!)
        if ($actor->getId() === $profileId) {
            return new AuthorizationResult(true, 'owner');
        }

        // Only admins can edit others
        if ($actor->hasRole('admin')) {
            return new AuthorizationResult(true, 'admin_privilege');
        }

        return new AuthorizationResult(false, 'no_edit_permission');
    }

    private function canDelete(User $actor, int $profileId): AuthorizationResult {
        // Nobody can delete their own account through this
        if ($actor->getId() === $profileId) {
            return new AuthorizationResult(false, 'self_delete_blocked');
        }

        // Only super_admin can delete accounts
        if ($actor->hasRole('super_admin')) {
            return new AuthorizationResult(true, 'super_admin');
        }

        return new AuthorizationResult(false, 'no_delete_permission');
    }
}

// Usage in controller
class ProfileController {
    private AuthorizationService $authz;
    private UserRepository $userRepo;

    public function __construct(AuthorizationService $authz, UserRepository $userRepo) {
        $this->authz = $authz;
        $this->userRepo = $userRepo;
    }

    public function updateProfile(int $profileId, array $data): JsonResponse {
        $actor = $this->getCurrentUser();

        // Always authorize before any action
        $result = $this->authz->authorize($actor, 'edit', 'user_profile', $profileId);

        if (!$result->isAllowed()) {
            return new JsonResponse(
                ['error' => 'Access denied'],
                403
            );
        }

        // Prevent privilege escalation: users can't edit their own role
        if ($actor->getId() === $profileId && isset($data['role'])) {
            unset($data['role']);
        }

        $this->userRepo->update($profileId, $data);

        return new JsonResponse(['status' => 'updated']);
    }
}
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Authentication Layer**: Verify user identity and session validity
